      "sha256": "17e318dccfadd6f37f024b595cee33aa985e90e203d97ac3c29fb322279ebc43",
      "source_region": "div#content",
      "text": "For any $n$ let $D_n$ be the set of sums of the shape $d_1,d_1+d_2,d_1+d_2+d_3,\\ldots$ where $1<d_1<d_2<\\cdots$ are the divisors of $n$. \n\nWhat is the size of $D_n\\backslash \\cup_{m<n}D_m$?\n\nIf $f(N)$ is the minimal $n$ such that $N\\in D_n$ then is it true that $f(N)=o(N)$? Perhaps just for almost all $N$?"
    }
  },
